tables.name: $tm.ppg
tables.description: This table is used to configure various settings for a PFC Priority Group attached to a port

key.name: $dev_port
key.description: The device port ID (a 9-bit value, for example 189) used to refer to a traffic port on a Tofino based system. The dev-port is the port designation used in the Tofino fixed-function API calls and in P4 programming.

key.name: $ppg_id
key.description: PFC Priority Group ID. Each ingressing packet can be mapped to a PFC Priority Group (PPG). The PPG will fall into one of two types: Default PPG or PPG in Tofino. An application maps traffic ingressing via a specified port to a PPG to provide the desired quality-of-service (QoS) characteristics to that traffic, such as lossless or real-time handling.

singleton.name: $icos_bitmap
singleton.description: A bitmap of ingress class of service, the packet priority class designation used to support PFC.

singleton.name: $lossless_enable
singleton.description: Enable/Disable lossless treatment for a PPG. The Default property of PPG is to treat traffic as lossy. Lossless traffic should not be dropped in TM except in worst-case scenarios when the upstream device is not honoring port pause or priority flow control, or when skid buffer space has been configured incorrectly.

singleton.name: $gmin_limit_cells
singleton.description: Guaranteed minimum limit for a PPG in terms of number of cells. For example, An allocation of 200 cells provides 200 x 80 bytes of buffering. This ensures at least 200 cells of buffer is available, regardless of buffer usage by other PPGs in the system. By default, the TM buffer is equally assigned to all the default PPGs and set to 0 for non-default PPGs.

singleton.name: $skid_limit_cells
singleton.description: PPG skid limit in terms of number of cells. The default value is 0. This buffer space is used when the PPGs configured ingress buffer limit has been used up. When traffic flow is directed to the skid buffer space, a PFC or Pause message is sent immediately to the upstream device.

singleton.name: $app_pool_limit_cells
singleton.description: Application pool limit cells for a PPG. By default, a PPG is not assigned to any application pool.

singleton.name: $ppg_hysteresis_cells
singleton.description: Hysteresis limit in terms of number of cells for a PPG. The default value is 0.

singleton.name: $app_pool_id
singleton.description: Application pool identifier. Used to assign an application pool to a PPG.

singleton.name: $app_pool_usage_enable
singleton.description: Enable/Disable application pool usage for a PPG.

singleton.name: $dynamic_baf
singleton.description: Dynamic Burst Absorption Factor value for a PPG. Used to decide how much of the available memory can be used for a PPG.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryAdd
supported_apis.description: This API programs a PPG for a port specified in the key field with the corresponding values specified in the data fields.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryMod
supported_apis.description: This API modifies an exisiting entry identified by a PPG for a port specified in the key field with the corresponding values specified in the data fields.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryGet
supported_apis.description: This API retrieves an entry identified by a PPG for a port specified in the key field and populates all the corresponding data fields.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryDel
supported_apis.description: This API resets all the data fields for the entry identified by the PPG and port specified in the key field.

tables.name: tof.tm.pool
tables.description: This table is used to configure various properties for pools.

singleton.name: size_cells
singleton.description: Used to specify the number of cells that need to be allocated for a particular pool.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryMod
supported_apis.description: This API is used to modify the size of the pool identified by the key field in terms of number of cells.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryGet
supported_apis.description: This API is used to fetch the current size of the pool identified by the key field in terms of number of cells.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryGetFirst
supported_apis.description: This API is used to fetch the name and the current size (in terms of number of cells) of the very first pool from the list of pools specified in the key field.

supported_apis.name: tableEntryGetNext_n
supported_apis.description: This API is used to fetch the names and the current sizes (in terms of number of cells) of the next n pools starting from the pool provided as an input parameter in the fixed order present in this json in the key field.

supported_apis.name: tableUsageGet
supported_apis.description: This API is used to fetch the current usage of the table in terms of number of entries. As this table has fixed number of entries, it will always return a constant value based on what all possible values the key field above can have.

tables.name: tof.tm.pool.skid
tables.description: This table is used to configure various properties for the skid pool.

singleton.name: resume_limit_cells
singleton.description: Used to specify the number of cells that will need to be freed up in order to resume the link pause or PFC.

supported_apis.name: tableDefaultEntrySet
supported_apis.description: This API is used to modify the current resume limit of the skid pool.

supported_apis.name: tableDefaultEntryReset
supported_apis.description: This API is used to reset the current resume limit of the skid pool to the initial value (0).

supported_apis.name: tableDefaultEntryGet
supported_apis.description: This API is used to fetch the current resume limit of the skid pool.

supported_apis.name: tableClear
supported_apis.description: This API is used to reset the current resume limit of the skid pool to the initial value (0).
